org.javimmutable.collections.listmap

Class JImmutableInsertOrderListMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.javimmutable.collections.listmap.JImmutableInsertOrderListMap<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<JImmutableMap.Entry<K,JImmutableList<V>>>, Insertable<JImmutableMap.Entry<K,V>,JImmutableListMap<K,V>>, InvariantCheckable, IterableStreamable<JImmutableMap.Entry<K,JImmutableList<V>>>, JImmutableListMap<K,V>, Mapped<K,JImmutableList<V>>, SplitableIterable<JImmutableMap.Entry<K,JImmutableList<V>>>, Streamable<JImmutableMap.Entry<K,JImmutableList<V>>>

    @Immutable
public class JImmutableInsertOrderListMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements Serializable
    JImmutableListMap implementation that allows keys to be traversed in the same order as they were inserted into the collection.
